Theo Walcott has been putting in some extra hours on the training pitch as the Arsenal winger looks to recover from the knee injury he suffered against Tottenham last season.

The 25-year-old has been out of action for for six months, but is targeting a return to Arsene Wenger's first team within the coming weeks.

Walcott took to Instagram to show off his sprinting skills on Wednesday afternoon as he went through his paces at Arsenal's London Colney training base.

