The winger seems to be happy with his progress as he posted: 'Getting #Stronger & #Quicker every day!!!! #SpeedMatters'.

Gunners fans will be hoping Walcott can return to action sooner rather than later as Wenger looks to better his team's fourth-placed finish of last season.

The French boss has signed former Barcelona star Alexis Sanchez to bolster his attack and Walcott revealed recently his delight at the new boy.

